Attributes attach to blocks too, as on the heading below.

## Styled heading {.featured #styled}

Per-item classes ride an inline span (`[text]{.class}`); carve-js drops a bare
`{.class}` line under an item, so the span form is what actually emits a class:

- [ ] [needs fixing]{.error}
- [x] [shipped]{.success}
